I needed a platter of tacos for a baby shower the next business day. Fortunately, Picante Taqueria said they were able to do it! We ordered about 25 steak tacos and 5 vegetarian tacos. They were DELICIOUS! The guests loved them -- especially my vegetarian friends who said these tacos were the best vegetarian tacos they've ever had. Thank you Picante Taqueria team for the high quality tacos and easy pickup process. *There were more salsas and toppings than just those seen in the picture.

Who knew a casual Saturday stroll through wicker would take me to THE BEST taco place I’ve EVER been to. We decided to go here on a whim after walking past many establishments. Once we walked in, we were met with the nicest owner who walked us through the absolute expression of flavors that he called a menu. Along with a detailed and lively explanation, came recommendations and samples galore. After exploring our options we landed on a chicken, steak and al pastor taco. To drink, horchata and watermelon fresca. On the patio we ate our tacos and with every bite we fell more and more in love. Our mouths were met with an explosion of flavor in each taco. The salsas were very authentic and flavorful and accented the flavors of the tacos perfectly. Just when we finished and were basking in the glory of the best food ever, Felipe brought out complimentary fresh watermelon with lime that was the perfect fresh dessert, especially on a hot day.  This was the best taco place I’ve ever been to, and my life has honestly been changed. I will be going back weekly to this restaurant. Truly a great experience and he has gained a lifelong customer.

I'm a Mexican native, born and raised. I'm a transplant to Wicker Park as of recently. I live right next door to this place and omg the food taste just like I'm at my mother's kitchen. The salsa taste just like my abuelas and the micheladas are 🔥 I've been here multiple times and the music makes me feel at home. When we asked for queso or something else to go with the chips, her response "this isn't American Mexican food." Well excuse me, this was the first time we have been here.   So the chips....We were served chips in a ziplock bag and salsa in a plastic to go cup. We asked for the salsa to be heated and the waitress seemed offended. My 2 stars applies to my taco dinner with chips and salsa which I somehow paid $18 for even though she told me the lunch special is $8 . The add on for the chips and salsa says $3 and some change. So somehow tax came out to $6. I think she charged me for chips and guacamole which is $7. This does not add up.  The only enjoyable part of my tacos were the corn tortillas. The steak had absolutely no flavor. There is absolutely nothing that seperatets this place's food from any other place. It reminded me of a flavorless version of El Burrito Loco in the suburbs. The rice wasn't anything different and the pinto beans were just plain boring. The chips and salsa we're pretty much what I expected after eating the tacos. Absolutely NOT $18 worth until the recipe is changed. Yes, I am highly disappointed.  However, I do want to say something positive about this place. The staff is very friendly. The lady who took my order was very nice. She seemed very friendly and she did greet me when I walked in. Also, the food didn't take long to receive which is always a positive. I very much enjoyed the music playing and the booth I sat in was very cool. It does seem like a fun atmosphere. I'm not saying I wouldn't return because now I know what to expect price range that is. I'm just really upset at the total cost of my meal and I personally felt like my order was bland.

Fine as a piece of fish but the flavor profile was basic at best. Average. Steak taco- was a complete disappointment. Not sure if it was marinated or seasoned with anything to be honest. Didn't finish. 2 hits one miss and one that was meh. Nice location but I show up for the food and it was a mixed bag. Any taco place should have kick ass steak tacos and kick ass this was not. Food was okay, but the parking lot next to the restaurant is a city parking trap. Left my car there for less than 1 minute to pick up my food, and there was a man putting a boot on my wheel as I was walking back up. They literally pay a person to sit in a turned off car and wait for anyone to leave their car unattended for the slightest moment. The restaurant is attached to the strip mall for the parking lot, so I didn't believe I was doing anything wrong, but the man forced me to walk to the nearest ATM and withdraw $140 for him to take the boot off. Sorry Picante, but I don't plan on ever eating at your restaurant again because of the sleazy thug-like company, Innovative Parking Solutions LLC.

For example, the $11 steak burrito wasn't seasoned at all, had low-quality meat, and when I asked for a fork they didn't have any to give out. Wife and I also tried the chips and guacamole; it was even worse. I think they used more onions than avocados. Won't be back any time soon.

Great little place to grab a quick bite.  The food is pretty good and it's fast.  They only have outdoor seating which means there is nowhere to sit in the winter. If you live in Chicago you know the best late night spots are these burrito shacks.  This place is pretty darn good when it comes to the burritos.  They have a decent amount of meat options you can choose and there are some sides to pick from.  I would rate this higher, but there  are just other burrito places that I think are better.  You may have to deal with being packed like sardines during the cold months.  The place is extremely small and just meant for a grab and go.  If you live in Wicker Park this will certainly do on your walk back from the night life. I will also not do not order the El Diablo Peppers unless you want to ruin you night or morning....

Picante Tacqueria was an integral part of my Wicker Park living experience. The steak burrito is fantastic.  Especially after several adult beverages.  I prolly ordered Picante once every week for a year and not once did it give me diarrhea.

I always pass this place on the way home and decided to pick up some food for lunch. I got the fish taco platter (grilled tilapia) and I have to say I wasn't all that impressed. It was a decent taco and the meal was filling but I've definitely had better. I was hoping for tamales but they said they didn't have any. I may try this place again and get something else, but there's a ton of better taco places in the neighborhood.

I ran across Picante's one day walking down Division.  It looks like a cute little taqueria with an orange/red sign doting three red, white, and green peppers.  In the warmer months it has a small outdoor eating area on the sidewalk.  When I say this place is small, I mean small!  You order at the counter and have to wait outside for them to call your order.  Picante's has great tacos and burritos though!! You can tell this is not your typical greasy Mexican food, but the ingredients are fresh.  The meat or fish is never greasy.  I usually order the fish option and the prices are cheap!

the burrito was good, but the front of the place says tamales and there were no tamalames.. on top of that they also advertised the breakfast burrito as served all day but when i asked they said they were not serving them. the patio was nice, but overall i probably would never be back
Love going to Picante for burritos! Veggie burrito is amazing and every bit as satisfying as their meaty friends. * Ask for extra spice if you want it to be hot, they run on the mild side.

If you want simple, no frills, authentic street tacos at any time (they are open after midnight), this is your place. The fish taco platter (grilled Tilapia w/ pico, black beans, Mexican rice and guac) for around $7, is awesome and highly recommended. The other menu items are great too, you won't be dissapointed.
great and cheap. burritos are alright. The price is right.

Hole in the wall place with great food.  Don't let the size fool you, great burritos, taco salads, fish tacos, etc...  The layered bean dip is worth the price, comes with their great chips.  Favorite is the chicken chipotle burrito, but combined with their hot salsa can be hot... caution!
